        entry
          antonyms (antonym opposite)
          definition "(strictly) A word whose meaning is the same as that of another word."
          synonyms (equivalent poecilonym)
        entry
          definition "A word or phrase with a meaning that is the same as, or very similar to, another word or phrase."
          example "“Happy” is a synonym of “glad”."
          synonyms (metonym)
        entry
          definition "Any of the formal names for a taxon, including the valid name (i.e. the senior synonym)."
        entry
          definition "Any name for a taxon, usually a validly published, formally accepted one, but often also an unpublished name."
        entry
          definition "An alternative (often shorter) name defined for an object in a database."
